# Kiosk Design System (iFCM)

All interfaces must match the self-service kiosk visual language. Source of truth: `shared/styles.css` (tokens in `:root`) and `shared/global.css` (utilities).

## Palette (strict)

| Token | Value | Usage |
|-------|-------|-------|
| `--color-navy` | `#1E1B4B` | Primary buttons, prices, headings |
| `--color-danger` | `#E11D48` | Cancel, destructive actions |
| `--color-bg` | `#F3F4F6` | Page background |
| `--color-text-muted` | `#6b7280` | Secondary text, labels |

Never use `#1A3B6E`, orange accent, or ad-hoc colors.

## Typography

- Font: `Montserrat` via Google Fonts
- Headings/CTAs: `font-weight: 700–800`, `letter-spacing: 0.03–0.06em`, `text-transform: uppercase` for section titles and primary buttons
- Prices: `font-weight: 800`, `color: var(--color-navy)`, `font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums`

## Components

- **Cards**: `border-radius: 16px`, `box-shadow: var(--shadow-card)`
- **Primary CTA**: navy pill (`border-radius: 9999px`), `box-shadow: var(--shadow-btn-navy)`, class `btn btn-primary btn-pill btn-press`
- **Cancel**: white + rose border (`btn-outline-danger`)
- **Tabs/switchers**: pill container, active segment = navy fill (see `.auth-tabs`, `.cat-tab`)
- **Footers**: sticky bottom bar with `box-shadow: var(--shadow-footer)`
- **Touch feedback**: always add `btn-press` on interactive elements

## Imports

```js
import '../shared/global.css'; // includes styles.css tokens
import './style.css';
```

HTML: include Montserrat from Google Fonts (see `client-lk/index.html`).

## Layout & spacing (UI/UX)

- Interface must feel **airy, clean, modern** — avoid cramped layouts.
- **Spacing grid**: multiples of 4px/8px. Use tokens: `--space-sm` (8px), `--space-md` (16px), `--space-lg` (24px).
- **Form blocks**: inputs must never stick to buttons or neighbors. Minimum gap between form sections — **16–24px**.
- **Label → input**: `--space-sm` (8px). **Between form groups**: `--space-md` (16px). **Last input → CTA button**: `--space-md` + `--space-sm` = **24px**.
- Use flex/grid containers with explicit `gap`, not margin hacks on individual fields.
- **Touch targets**: inputs and buttons `min-height: 44–48px` on mobile.

### Form pattern

```html
<div class="auth-fields"> <!-- or .form-stack -->
  <div class="form-group">...</div>
  <button class="btn btn-primary btn-pill">Submit</button>
</div>
```

```css
.auth-fields { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: var(--space-md); }
.auth-fields .btn { margin-top: var(--space-sm); } /* +8px → 24px before CTA */
.form-group { gap: var(--space-sm); }
```
